SR NO. 65 ENROLLED
WHEREAS, Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity was originally chartered and incorporated
as Kappa Alpha Nu on May 15, 1911, and the name was changed to Kappa Alpha Psi by a
resolution offered and adopted at the Grand Chapter meeting in December 1914, which
became effective April 15, 1915; and
WHEREAS, except for the years of World War I and World War II, during which
time several Grand Chapter meetings were suspended, Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity embarked
upon an era of expansion and growth; and
WHEREAS, Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity, Inc., is now organizationally and
administratively mature, and the fraternity steadily moves toward a tomorrow of promise,
productivity, and influence.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
does hereby designate Wednesday, April 8, 2026, as "Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity, Inc. Day"
at the Louisiana State Capitol and does hereby extend its sincerest wishes that the
organization continue to prosper in all of its endeavors for many years to come.
PRESIDENT OF THE SENATE
